reviewText: Grandson fascinated with dinosaurs so get everything dinosaur for him.  Have not seen it myself so can't comment on content.

My 3 Year-Old loves Dinosaur Train, and we got a series of these DVD's for a long road trip.  They were awesome and he was in heaven.  We got a few of the Dinosaur Train figurines to accompany him in his car seat, and he loved it!  These DVD's are structured just like the TV shows, but run back-to-back with multiple episodes.  Two thumbs up!

My 3 year old picked this video out and we had only seen the show once or twice. I was amazed at how educational this show is.  The kids (my 3 year old and his 5 year old brother) have both become dinosaur experts!  Everyone in our family has become Dinosaur Train fans.

Great video for kids. My 15 month old son loves it. The colors are great, the water looks almost real and the music keeps him dancing. What would we do without Mr the Conductor?Dinosaur Train: T.rex Tales

Got this for my grandson for his 4th birthday.  He saw some stars in an unrelated book today and let me know those are constellations.  When asked how he knew that, he said, "PBS.org."  (Credit to the Dinosaur Train!) Impressive! He very much likes this video.

Our 3.5 year old son is obsessed with trains and just starting to like dinosaurs. He had seen 'Dinosaur Train' on PBS a couple of times and liked it. I ordered this DVD as a special car treat for our 1700 mile trip this summer. He absolutely loved it! Nothing like hearing your 3 year old giggling in the backseat on a long trip. There were also quite a few episodes in the DVD, which was awesome.

 We're going to suggest other 'Dinosaur Train' DVDs as gift ideas for his birthday.
a god send for cold and or rainey days

My great nephew is a big fan of this show (he's two) so I was excited to see this DVD available as his favorite character is the little T-Rex named Buddy is featured.  Thanks so much, a little boy really enjoyed one of his Christmas presents.

My 4 year old just loves dinosaur train. He really learns a lot from it. And I have learned a lot of dinosaur names from it also. I ordered all of the DVDs.  Much Better than your typical useless cartoons
Sent this to my Granddaughter in CA, her three older cousins love the Dinosaur Train series so I knew it would be a hit with her, it was!
I purchased this dvd as a gift for one of my grandchildren.  It is one of his favorite shows.  The product was exactly as expected.

These are NOT like Dino Dan, but still good and somewhat educational. These are animated episodes about a dinosaur family where the kids take a time traveling train to learn about dinosaurs in various time periods. My kids, ages 6 and 2, really like them.

I purchased this DVD for a gift so I didn't actually watch it..  But I have seen other Dinosaur Train episodes and I really enjoy them. They are educational and entertaining. I have an 8 month old son and I secretly hope that he will become interested in this show and the characters. ;-)
My 2 yr old can't get enough of dinosaurs.. needless to say he is very pleased with this dvd and we watch it daily.
This is my 6 month old's favorite TV show. :) She loved the book and all of her Dinosaur Train collection! :)
This DVD really teaches my kids a lot about dinosaurs in a relatable way.  They love to watch all the stories.

Purchased for my 5 year old grandson. He loves these when he tires of watching "real" dino dvds.
Very entertaining and actually informative.

My 2 year old (soon to be 3) LOVES Dinosaur Train!  The stories are so cute and educational.  We don't let our son watch actual TV so these PBS videos are great to give him the down time while teaching him things all at the same time.  As a parent I always feel comfortable allowing him to watch Dinosaur Train.  Never anything scary or inappropriate.
